      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ALL OVER IT (10) opened his career in the best possible manner last start, scoring by 18 metres over 2150m at Bendigo. May just need a bit of luck at some point from this difficult draw. Steps up a level but he will benefit from that last run and is capable of running another big race. OUTBACK QUEENIE (2) scored at Maryborough two runs ago before having her colours lowered when second at her latest appearance over 2195m at Ararat, beaten 2 metres. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets some better types this time but she has the ability to test this field. HELLOVATIME (12) comes right into contention after scoring last start by 5.5 metres at this track over 2190m. NOMORELYING (8) disappointed last time but is a chance based on a good second over 1650m at Bendigo two runs back.",
